    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "In this experiment we learned to measure the unknown resistance and capacitance of two components using a Capacitor Comparison Bridge, which in some regards can be considered a variation of the Wheatstone Bridge designed to use an AC source by including additional impedances in equilibrium. Like in previous bridges we can calculate the value of the resistance and the capacitance simply by balancing the bridge using both potentiometers."
