    }), "\n", _jsxs(_components.p, {
      children: ["When we press the button, the measured current that the MOC3021 uses is 24.6 mA while the auxiliary triac Q4004L4 is driving a current of 3.46 A directly from the AC (120V 60Hz) alternator used by the lamp. We need the auxiliary triac since the datasheet specifies that we can’t use the MOC3021 directly to power loads that draw from an AC source and it is limited to an absolute maximum rating of 50mA.\nMOC3021 Datasheet:\n", _jsx(_components.a, {
