    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "In this experiment we learned the importance of reading the electrical maximum ratings of every component we use since the optocoupler of the circuit will be damaged if we tried to drive the current that the lamp draws from the AC source directly from the MOC3021 triac.\nQuestions Worksheet 4\nIn your own words, what are the objectives and the procedure of the practice?\nThe main objective was to learn how to use optocouplers as circuit isolators and their different circuit configurations based on the type of optocoupler used (Transistor Based, SCR, TRIAC etc). The procedure of the three experiments done involved assembling the optocoupler configuration circuits for the 4N26, PC817 and MOC3021 and testing their behavior depending on their input voltage and current and what the current needed by the device they needed to power.\nExplain in your own words what an optocoupler is and what is its main function?\nAn optocoupler is a device that allows an electrical signal to be transmitted between two isolated circuits, their properties are useful since they can isolate low voltage devices from high voltage circuits, this is essential to be able to avoid damage or disruptions from high voltage surges. They can also be used with triacs to drive large AC voltages from small digital signals and are a tool that can be used to remove electrical noise from signals.\nWhat are the two main parts of an optocoupler?\nA transmitter diode, usually a LED or IRED, that encodes the incoming signal into light and receiver, usually a photosensor diode, that decodes the incoming light signal form the transmitter.\nDescribe at least two types of optocouplers\nTwo types of optocouplers are TRIAC based and SCR based optocouplers, both can use GaAs infrared LED as their transmitter but differ on their photosensitive part, the first uses a TRIAC or triode for alternating current that can conduct current in either direction when triggered, intended to be used with devices that draw from an AC line, while the second uses a SCR or silicon-controlled rectifier and can only conduct current in one direction."
